---
import ProjectLayout from "../../components/ProjectLayout.astro";
import TechIcon from "../../components/TechIcon.astro";
---

<ProjectLayout
  title="ImmoScout24 Austria — Search Platform"
  description="Case study: contributing to Austria's top 3 real estate search platform with fully tested distributed microservices"
>
  <main>
    <section
      class="project-hero"
      style="background: var(--hero-bg); color: white; padding: 5rem 0 3.5rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; text-align: center; position: relative;"
    >
      <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px;">
        <h1
          style="font-size: 3rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; letter-spacing: -0.02em;"
        >
          ImmoScout24 Austria
        </h1>
        <p
          style="font-size: 1.35rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); max-width: 700px; margin: 0 auto 2rem; line-height: 1.6;"
        >
          Search, listing, SEO, and marketing automation work inside a tested
          distributed real-estate platform
        </p>
        <div
          style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;"
        >
          <span
            style="padding: 0.5rem 1.25rem; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); border-radius: 50px; font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.85rem; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.15);"
          >
            LIVE
          </span>
          <a
            href="https://github.com/calindotgabriel/immobile-search"
            style="padding: 0.5rem 1.25rem; background: white; color: #0f172a; border-radius: 50px; font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.85rem; text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.2s ease;"
          >
            Demo repo
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <article style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px;">

      <!-- THE PROBLEM -->
      <section
        class="content-section"
        style="background: var(--gradient-card); border-radius: 20px; padding: 3rem 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);"
      >
        <h2
          style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--text);"
        >
          The Problem
        </h2>
        <p
          style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;"
        >
          ImmoScout24 is one of the most-used real-estate platforms in Austria and part
          of the wider Scout24 group. The work sat inside a mature distributed system:
          search and listing flows, SEO-sensitive pages, marketing automation, and
          integration points that had to keep working under normal product delivery pressure.
        </p>
        <p
          style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text-muted);"
        >
          The existing system already had strong unit, integration, and e2e coverage.
          My contribution was not a rewrite. It was the work of getting productive in
          that environment, making targeted changes, and matching the team's expectations
          for testing, review quality, and production safety.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- THE CHALLENGE -->
      <section
        class="content-section"
        style="background: var(--gradient-card); border-radius: 20px; padding: 3rem 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);"
      >
        <h2
          style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--text);"
        >
          My Biggest Challenge
        </h2>
        <p
          style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;"
        >
          The steepest learning curve was adapting to the quality expectations of a
          DAX-listed engineering organization. The codebase was tested at every layer
          across distributed services, with SSO federated from Scout24's German platform.
          Small changes still required clear reasoning, good test coverage, and careful review.
        </p>
        <p
          style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text-muted);"
        >
          I had to level up my testing discipline, communicate more precisely with senior
          engineers, and learn when to sync with my mentor. That calibration mattered:
          ask too early and you create noise; wait too long and you block delivery.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- WHAT I DELIVERED -->
      <section
        class="content-section"
        style="background: var(--gradient-card); border-radius: 20px; padding: 3rem 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);"
      >
        <h2
          style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 2rem; color: var(--text);"
        >
          What I Delivered
        </h2>

        <div
          class="features-grid"
          style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 2rem;"
        >
          <div
            style="padding: 2rem; background: var(--card-soft-bg); border-radius: 16px; border: 1px solid var(--pill-border);"
          >
            <h3
              style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--primary);"
            >
              UX Improvements
            </h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.6;">
              Shipped focused improvements in search and listing flows, with changes
              reviewed against an existing product and testing culture rather than a
              greenfield codebase.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div
            style="padding: 2rem; background: var(--card-soft-bg); border-radius: 16px; border: 1px solid var(--pill-border);"
          >
            <h3
              style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--primary);"
            >
              SEO-Sensitive Delivery
            </h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.6;">
              Worked on technical SEO changes where page structure, rendering behavior,
              and release quality had direct product impact. The team tracked organic
              visibility closely, so regressions had to be avoided.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div
            style="padding: 2rem; background: var(--card-soft-bg); border-radius: 16px; border: 1px solid var(--pill-border);"
          >
            <h3
              style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--primary);"
            >
              Marketing Automation (Iterable)
            </h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.6;">
              Integrated Iterable so marketing teams could run targeted campaigns and
              automate lifecycle messaging without depending on engineering for every
              campaign change.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div
            style="padding: 2rem; background: var(--card-soft-bg); border-radius: 16px; border: 1px solid var(--pill-border);"
          >
            <h3
              style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--primary);"
            >
              Enricher Task Upgrades
            </h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.6;">
              Upgraded the functional programming-style enricher tasks that
              process and transform property data — improving reliability
              and maintainability of the data pipeline.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- BUSINESS IMPACT -->
      <section
        class="content-section"
        style="background: var(--gradient-card); border-radius: 20px; padding: 3rem 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);"
      >
        <h2
          style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--text);"
        >
          Business Impact
        </h2>

        <div
          class="metrics-grid"
          style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr)); gap: 2rem; margin: 2.5rem 0;"
        >
          <div
            style="text-align: center; padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--card-soft-bg); border-radius: 16px; border: 1px solid var(--pill-border);"
          >
            <div
              style="font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"
            >
              Top 3
            </div>
            <div style="color: var(--text-muted); font-weight: 500;">
              Most-Used Listing Platform in AT
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            style="text-align: center; padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--card-soft-bg); border-radius: 16px; border: 1px solid var(--pill-border);"
          >
            <div
              style="font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"
            >
              ATH
            </div>
            <div style="color: var(--text-muted); font-weight: 500;">
              SEO Performance Improved
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            style="text-align: center; padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--card-soft-bg); border-radius: 16px; border: 1px solid var(--pill-border);"
          >
            <div
              style="font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"
            >
              20%
            </div>
            <div style="color: var(--text-muted); font-weight: 500;">
              Higher User Engagement
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p
          style="font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text-muted); margin-top: 1.5rem;"
        >
          The impact was practical: SEO changes supported organic visibility, UX work
          contributed to engagement, and Iterable reduced the amount of engineering effort
          needed for marketing campaigns. Some exact business metrics are not mine to
          disclose in detail, so I keep the public proof focused on the work I owned and
          the production context it shipped into.
        </p>
        <p
          style="font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text-muted); margin-top: 1rem;"
        >
          For a contract buyer, the useful signal is not a greenfield demo. It is evidence
          that I can enter a mature system, respect the quality bar, and ship targeted
          product/integration changes without increasing release risk.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- WHAT I LEARNED -->
      <section
        class="content-section"
        style="background: var(--gradient-card); border-radius: 20px; padding: 3rem 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);"
      >
        <h2
          style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--text);"
        >
          What I Took Away
        </h2>
        <p
          style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;"
        >
          This project changed my default expectations for test coverage and review quality.
          A fully tested distributed system does not remove the need for judgment; it gives
          good engineers the confidence to make smaller, better-scoped changes.
        </p>
        <p
          style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text-muted);"
        >
          On the human side, I learned when to reach out to a mentor and when to push
          through on my own. That calibration — knowing when to sync and when to execute —
          is something I now consider a core part of how I operate in any team.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- TECH STACK -->
      <section
        class="content-section"
        style="background: var(--gradient-card); border-radius: 20px; padding: 3rem 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);"
      >
        <h2
          style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 2rem; color: var(--text);"
        >
          Technology Stack
        </h2>
        <div
          style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(140px, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem;"
        >
          {
            [
              { name: "React", tech: "React" },
              { name: "Hapi.js", tech: "Hapi" },
              { name: "Node.js", tech: "Node.js" },
              { name: "MongoDB", tech: "MongoDB" },
              { name: "AWS", tech: "AWS" },
              { name: "Iterable", tech: "JavaScript" },
            ].map((item) => (
              <div style="padding: 1.25rem 1rem; background: var(--hero-bg); color: white; border-radius: 16px; font-weight: 600; text-align: center; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); transition: all 0.3s ease; display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; min-height: 100px; justify-content: center;">
                <TechIcon technology={item.tech} size={32} />
                <span style="font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.2;">
                  {item.name}
                </span>
              </div>
            ))
          }
        </div>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>
</ProjectLayout>

<style>
  .project-hero h1 {
    color: white;
  }

  .content-section {
    animation: fadeInUp 0.6s ease forwards;
  }

  @keyframes fadeInUp {
    from {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(30px);
    }
    to {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(0);
    }
  }

  .features-grid > div:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    transition: transform 0.3s ease;
  }

  .content-section div[style*="min-height: 100px"]:hover {
    transform: translateY(-3px);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 25px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .project-hero {
      padding: 48px 0 32px;
    }

    .project-hero h1 {
      font-size: 2.25rem;
    }

    .project-hero p {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
    }

    .content-section {
      padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
    }

    .metrics-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .features-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .content-section div[style*="repeat(auto-fill, minmax(140px, 1fr))"] {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(110px, 1fr)) !important;
      gap: 1rem !important;
    }

    .content-section div[style*="min-height: 100px"] {
      min-height: 80px !important;
      padding: 1rem 0.75rem !important;
    }

    .content-section div[style*="min-height: 100px"] span:first-child {
      font-size: 1.5rem !important;
    }

    .content-section div[style*="min-height: 100px"] span:last-child {
      font-size: 0.8rem !important;
    }
  }
</style>
